COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: ORANGE COUNTY ALMANAC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 For the first time anybody could remember, movie-makers came to the Seal Beach 
Naval Weapons Station this month to shoot a scene for a feature film. 
</P>
<P>
 Director Ron Howard spent several hours at the base filming a scene for 
"Apollo 13," a Universal Pictures movie about the near-disastrous 1970 moon 
mission. 
</P>
<P>
 Lead actor Tom Hanks was also at the base with co-stars to film a farewell 
scene. 
</P>
<P>
 Station spokesman Joe Davidson said movie-makers had looked at the base for 
filming before but they changed their minds and went elsewhere. 
</P>
<P>
 Today 
</P>
<P>
 Jerome Bettis, Los Angeles Rams running back and last year's NFL Rookie of the 
Year, will host a Monday night football party at 6 p.m. at Planet Hollywood in 
Santa Ana. 
</P>
<P>
 Those attending the event are encouraged to wear Rams clothing. Proceeds from 
the party will go to various Orange County charities. 
</P>
<P>
 Bettis will sign a Rams jersey that will go on display at the restaurant. 
</P>
<P>
 Planet Hollywood is located at 1641 Sunflower Ave. For more information, call 
(714) 668-1440. 
</P>
