<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: PLACENTIA/YORBA LINDA; DISTRICT STUDYING STUDENTS' SIDE 
TRIPS TO THEME PARKS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DANIELLE FOUQUETTE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Students attending competitions, conventions and other extended field trips 
might no longer be allowed to take side trips to visit amusement parks. 
</P>
<P>
 Placentia-Yorba Linda Unified School District officials began a review of the 
district's policy on extended field trips at the request of school board 
President Judy Miner. 
</P>
<P>
 The issue of side trips to nearby amusement parks on weekend field trips came 
up at Tuesday's board meeting during discussion of two planned Esperanza High 
School field trips. 
</P>
<P>
 Field trips of more than one day must be approved by the board, which usually 
does so with little comment. But last week Miner questioned side trips to 
Disneyland and Knott's Berry Farm being planned for students attending a 
weekend journalism convention in Anaheim next month and a side trip to Marine 
World Africa USA for students participating in a band competition in Northern 
California in November. 
</P>
<P>
 "I am nervous about students spending the evening at amusement parks," which 
are difficult to supervise, Miner said. 
</P>
<P>
 The board approved both trips, but asked district officials to determine if 
the side trips violate any board policy and to weigh potential liability 
problems. DANIELLE FOUQUETTE 
</P>
</TEXT>
