<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: RANCHO SANTA MARGARITA; S. COUNTY CHAMBERS ORGANIZATION 
MOVES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 After eight years in Laguna Hills, the South Orange County Chambers of 
Commerce has moved to a new suite of offices in a new city. 
</P>
<P>
 The chamber group recently began operating out of an office in the Plaza 
Empressa, at 29941 Aventura, Suite I at Santa Margarita Parkway and Via 
Empressa. 
</P>
<P>
 With their lease expiring in Laguna Hills at the end of August, chamber 
officials made a decision to move when the Santa Margarita Co. came up with an 
offer for a lease in Rancho Santa Margarita just last month. 
</P>
<P>
 The Santa Margarita Co. "made a pretty good offer," said Barbara Thomas, 
director of operations for SOCCC. 
</P>
<P>
 Terms of the lease weren't disclosed, but Santa Margarita Co. officials said 
the two sides agreed on a six-month agreement with the possibility of a longer 
commitment. 
</P>
<P>
 "We believe we made a very competitive and attractive offer," said Santa 
Margarita Co. spokeswoman Diane Gaynor. "I think we're all very happy with it." 
</P>
<P>
 Although concern has been expressed about poor accessibility of the office's 
Rancho Santa Margarita location, SOCCC officials said chamber members will be 
pleasantly surprised at the new office's proximity to the Saddleback Valley. 
</P>
<P>
 With the Foothill Transportation Corridor being built near the chamber site 
and several access roads opening or scheduled to open, Rancho Santa Margarita 
is becoming more centrally located in South County, chamber officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 "Its accessibility to other major South Orange County business centers via 
both (Interstate 5) and the Foothill Transportation Corridor made it a logical 
site for our new headquarters," SOCCC Executive Director Kate Keena said. FRANK 
MESSINA 
</P>
</TEXT>
