<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: GARDEN GROVE; DRAINAGE WORK TO IMPEDE TRAFFIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BERT ELJERA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Southbound traffic on Magnolia Street between Westminster and Bestel avenues 
will be reduced to one lane beginning this week until January because of 
improvements to the area's drainage system. 
</P>
<P>
 The construction will take place between 7:30 a.m. and 4 p.m. Motorists are 
urged to use alternative routes during these hours. 
</P>
<P>
 Parking in the area will be restricted, but access to businesses and 
residences along the construction area will be maintained, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 City Engineer Bill Patapoff said that a storm drain is being constructed to 
prevent flooding at the Magnolia-Bestel intersection. 
</P>
<P>
 The $889,000 project includes installation of concrete pipes, catch basins and 
street work at the intersection, Patapoff said. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, contact John Ompad, the project engineer, at (714) 
741-5178. BERT ELJERA 
</P>
</TEXT>
