<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: LOS ALAMITOS; CITY PERSONNEL PANEL APPOINTMENTS MADE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BERT ELJERA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Charles Landon and Donald Sherrin have been reappointed to four-year terms on 
the Personnel Appeals Commission, a five-member board that hears appeals of 
employees who have been fired, suspended, demoted or disciplined. And the City 
Council last week also appointed Betty Schmicker-Black to the panel. 
</P>
<P>
 Landon and Sherrin are both incumbents, their terms having expired Aug. 31. 
Along with Schmicker-Black, they will now serve until August, 1998. 
</P>
<P>
 The other members of the commission are Viki Howard and Tom Rothwell, whose 
terms will expire in 1996. 
</P>
<P>
 The council last week also appointed Kathie L. Matsuyama to fill a vacancy in 
the Parks and Recreation Commission. She will serve until Dec. 31, 1996. 
</P>
<P>
 Landon, 39, human resources manager at Arrowhead Water in Monterey Park, has 
been a Los Alamitos resident for the past seven years. 
</P>
<P>
 Schmicker-Black, 42, works at Cal State Long Beach's Career Development 
Center. She moved to Los Alamitos with her family this year. 
</P>
<P>
 "I was looking for an opportunity to get involved," Schmicker-Black said. 
"This was the best fit for my experience." BERT ELJERA 
</P>
</TEXT>
