COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: GARDEN GROVE; GANG UNIT ARRESTS 220 OVER FIVE-WEEK SPAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARTIN MILLER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A special five-week gang detail netted more than 220 gang-related arrests 
during August and September, police said last week. 
</P>
<P>
 The 15-officer unit logged arrests including one for homicide, four for 
robbery, seven for auto theft, 12 for felonious assault and 20 for firearms 
violations, Garden Grove Police Lt. Kevin Raney said.The detail also seized 20 
guns and recovered seven stolen vehicles, Raney said. 
</P>
<P>
 Seven additional police officers were transferred to the department's gang 
suppression unit Aug. 5 to curb growing gang activity in the city, Raney said. 
The department disbanded the special detail Sept. 9, Raney said. 
</P>
<P>
 "We wanted to make sure we had a safe, quiet start to school," he said. 
</P>
<P>
 Typically, gang activity increases during the summer and falls off when school 
begins, Raney said.MARTIN MILLER 
