<HEADLINE>
<P>
5 ARRESTED AT HOUSE IN LANCASTER; CRIME: DEPUTIES RESPONDING TO A CALL ABOUT A 
LOUD PARTY FIND A PIPE BOMB, SAWED-OFF SHOTGUN AND DRUGS. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEANNETTE REGALADO, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Three adults and two teen-agers were arrested after sheriff's deputies found 
weapons and drugs at a Lancaster house during a routine call about a loud 
party, authorities said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles County sheriff's deputies reported discovering a homemade pipe 
bomb, a sawed-off shotgun and unspecified amounts of methamphetamine and 
marijuana about 9 p.m. after they responded to a neighbor's complaint of a loud 
party in the 44000 block of 40th St. West. 
</P>
<P>
 Scott Shows, 21, who lives at the house, was arrested on suspicion of 
possessing controlled substances, a sawed-off shotgun and an explosive device, 
said Lt. Daniel Castillo of the Antelope Valley Sheriff's Station. He is being 
held in lieu of $500,000 at the station's jail, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 Penny Bowen, 24, of Quartz Hill, and Marjorie Richardson, 29, of Palmdale, 
were arrested on suspicion of being under the influence of a stimulant, 
Castillo said. Bowen was cited and released. Richardson is being held on a 
previous warrant. Her bail is set at $3,500. 
</P>
<P>
 Two 16-year-old girls from Palmdale and Quartz Hill also were arrested on 
suspicion of being under the influence of illegal drugs, Castillo said. 
</P>
<P>
 "We were called there to tell them to turn down the loud music," Castillo 
said. "It was a routine party call until we found the pipe bomb." 
</P>
<P>
 When deputies arrived at the house, a couple of party-goers ran from the 
scene, Castillo said. While they spoke with one of the minors arrested, 
deputies noticed expended .22-caliber rifle casings in the front yard. 
</P>
<P>
 "They conducted a search of the house and noticed the shotgun and white 
powdery substance and the marijuana," Castillo said. 
</P>
<P>
 In a more in-depth search, they found the pipe bomb and evacuated the house 
until bomb squad investigators could dispose of it, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 An investigation is continuing, Castillo said. 
</P>
