SOUTHLAND PREVIEW / THE BUSINESS WEEK AHEAD: LOS ANGELES COUNTY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Pacific Rim Conference: The region will take center stage in Los Angeles this 
week as delegates from Japan, Korea and Mexico meet to discuss trade and 
technology issues at the 20th annual Century of the Pacific Conference. The 
four-day meeting begins Tuesday and is hosted by the Los Angeles Junior Chamber 
of Commerce.It will feature presentations by U.S. Secretary of Commerce Ronald 
H. Brown, Los Angeles Mayor Richard Riordan and California Secretary of Trade 
and Commerce Julie Wright. The conference is designed as an international 
educational forum for business, community and political leaders. It will focus 
on the impact of the Pacific Rim trade and technology industries on the global 
economy. Conference events are scheduled at various Downtown Los Angeles sites, 
including the Hyatt Regency Los Angeles and the Downtown Hilton Hotel. 
</P>
