</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Business Forum: The recently formed Southern California/Arizona Region of the 
Council for Continuous Improvement will hold one in a series of regional forums 
for local businesses at 9 a.m. Thursday at the Ontario Marriott. The 
Ontario-based regional group, affiliated with the Council for Continuous 
Improvement in San Jose, was formed to accommodate a growing membership in 
Southern California and Arizona, according to CCI officials.The council, a 
national nonprofit organization, was formed in 1989 to help businesses work 
together on common problems and find ways to improve their operations. "One of 
the successes we're already seeing in the region is that through the CCI 
networking and use of our training materials, some of the members have cut 
their training costs by sharing training resources with each other," said Bill 
Nipp, regional manager for the group. 
