<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: LABOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Union Approves Lucky Stores Contract: About 1,700 warehouse employees and 
drivers overwhelmingly approved a contract Sunday that guarantees them job 
security and a raise of $1.70 an hour during the next four years.The vote ends 
the threat of a strike that would have interrupted deliveries to 235 Southland 
Lucky supermarkets. A strike set for last week had been stalled while 
negotiators worked out the new terms. About 92% of the members voted to accept 
the contract terms, but Ed J. Mireles, head of Teamsters Union Local 952 in 
Orange, would not release the numerical tally. The contract covers workers at 
warehouses in Buena Park, Fullerton and Irvine. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA091994-0158 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 080750 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
September 19, 1994, Monday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
