<P>
 Bankrupt Firms' Debt Rises: The total debt of bankrupt Japanese companies in 
August grew 17.9% from a year earlier to $4.94 billion, according to a private 
research company. Tokyo Commerce and Industry Research Co. said businesses 
continued to suffer because of the strong yen, price competition and changes in 
consumer tastes. The number of bankruptcy cases was down 8.9% from a year 
earlier, to 1,083. 
