<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: SIMI VALLEY; FREE DISPOSAL OF HEAVY TRASH SUNDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRISTINA LIMA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Simi Valley residents will be able to get rid of heavy trash such as 
appliances, asphalt, clean concrete and green waste during a free 
trash-disposal day Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 Residents will be able to drop off items at the Simi Valley Landfill and 
Recycling Center at 2801 Madera Road from 10 a.m. to 4 p.m. Items must be in 
separate containers and covered so they do not spill. 
</P>
<P>
 Residents must prove that they are Simi Valley residents by bringing a 
driver's license with a local address. They must also unload their own 
vehicles. CHRISTINA LIMA 
</P>
</TEXT>
